    <Value type="list" instance="1" index="241" genre="config" label="Button #1 Programmable" value="0" min="0" max="5" size="1" write_only="true">
      <Help>Default Mode – The button on the Minimote uses the factory default functions for operation instead of any special functionality related to the below modes. Scene Mode – The button on the Minimote executes a scene from data received for Parameters Numbers 0-239 related to the button being pressed. Add Mode – The button on the Minimote is able to include/add devices into the Z-Wave network. Remove Mode – The button on the Minimote is able to remove devices from the Z-Wave network. Association Mode – The button on the Minimote is able to associate one device to another. Learn Mode – The button on the Minimote is able to allow the Minimote to be included into other Z-Wave networks and to learn Z-Wave network information.</Help>
      <Item label="Default Mode" value="0" />
      <Item label="Scene Mode" value="1" />
